article.description: Grandy Glaze scored 20 points and Grand Canyon won its sixth-straight game with a 74-53 victory over Bethune-Cookman on Sunday night.
article.headline: Glaze scores 20; Grand Canyon beats Bethune-Cookman 74-53
article.linkText: Glaze scores 20; Grand Canyon beats Bethune-Cookman 74-53
article.story: PHOENIX -- Grandy Glaze scored 20 points and Grand Canyon won its sixth-straight game with a 74-53 victory over Bethune-Cookman on Sunday night. Glaze was 10 of 13 from the floor and grabbed eight rebounds to lead Grand Canyon (13-2). The Antelopes are 9-1 at home and open their Western Athletic Conference schedule at home against New Mexico State on Saturday. Dominic Magee had 13 points, and DeWayne Russell and Joshua Braun added 12 for Grand Canyon. Mario Moody scored 15 points and Ricky Johnson added 11 for Bethune-Cookman (4-11), which has lost seven straight. Glaze had 10 points and Braun six as the Antelopes built a 36-22 halftime lead. Johnson made back-to-back 3-pointers to pull the Wildcats to 42-32 early in the second half. Grand Canyon answered with a 14-4 spurt and cruised from there. Magee scored eight points with two 3s, and Braun had four points during the span.
